translated: Alen, Alvin Agaton, dentist, Gothenburg, b. December 10, 1888 in Gothenburg to city chemist, PhD J. E. A. and Anna Lundmark. Married to Anna Hinke in 1917. Children: Bertil, b. 1918, Bengt, b. 1920. Completed high school at Gothenburg Latin School in 1909, graduated from dental school in 1911, became a licensed dentist in 1914. Went on a study trip to Berlin in 1914. Has been practicing dentistry in Gothenburg since 1915. Secretary of the Gothenburg Dental Society from 1923-1925 and 1929-1930, librarian and conservator from 1917-1936, conservator from 1937-1946, chairman in 1935-1936, and concurrent chairman of the Swedish Dental Society's local chapter. Chairman of the Gothenburg Shooting District from 1922-1924, deputy chairman of the Gothenburg and Bohus Shooting Association and its representative in the Swedish Shooting Federation, chairman of the Göta Par Bricoles singing choir, and member of the Swedish Sports Shooting Association and other organizations. Has received several honorary awards.

structured.description: Alvin Agaton Alen was a Swedish dentist born in Gothenburg on December 10, 1888. He studied at the Gothenburg Latin School and graduated from dental school in 1911. Alen went on a study trip to Berlin in 1914 and has been practicing dentistry in Gothenburg since 1915. He was secretary of the Gothenburg Dental Society, librarian, conservator, and chairman of the Swedish Dental Society's local chapter. Alen was also involved in several shooting organizations and received several honorary awards.
